@startuml fig-osi-layers
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12

title The OSI Reference Model — Seven Layers

rectangle "**7 — Application**\nUser-facing services\n(HTTP, FTP, SMTP, DNS)" as L7 #E1BEE7
rectangle "**6 — Presentation**\nData representation\n(TLS, UTF-8, JSON, ASN.1)" as L6 #E1BEE7
rectangle "**5 — Session**\nDialogue management\n(session setup, teardown)" as L5 #E1BEE7
rectangle "**4 — Transport**\nProcess-to-process delivery\n(TCP segment / UDP datagram)" as L4 #C8E6C9
rectangle "**3 — Network**\nEnd-to-end packet delivery\n(IP packet)" as L3 #BBDEFB
rectangle "**2 — Data Link**\nNode-to-node frame transfer\n(Ethernet frame)" as L2 #E3F2FD
rectangle "**1 — Physical**\nBit transmission\n(electrical / optical / radio signal)" as L1 #F5F5F5

L7 -down-> L6
L6 -down-> L5
L5 -down-> L4
L4 -down-> L3
L3 -down-> L2
L2 -down-> L1

legend right
  The OSI model organises network
  communication into seven layers.
  Each layer provides services to
  the layer above and consumes
  services from the layer below.
endlegend
@enduml
